FBIS4-22133 "jptot017__l94073" JPRS-TOT-94-017-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 16 April 1994 WEST EUROPE TURKEY Paper Reports Kurdish Tribes Join Forces Against PKK Paper Reports Kurdish Tribes Join Forces Against PKK NC2204170394 Istanbul MILLIYET in Turkish 16 Apr 94 p 13 NC2204170394 Istanbul MILLIYET Turkish BFN [Text] The renowned Jirki, Gevdan, Mamguran, Giravi, and Goran tribes in Sirnak and Hakkari Provinces have joined their forces against the Kurdish Workers Party [PKK]. The tribes, which have thousands of armed men, assembled in Beytussebap District to demonstrate against the PKK at 1030 yesterday. Some 5,000 demonstrators marched and chanted: "The banner will not be lowered; the cause cannot be abandoned; the Turkish, Kurdish, Laz [Black Sea people], and Circassian peoples are brothers; this country will be the PKK's grave; the PKK will drown in the blood it sheds."
